The horse you speak of does not exist.

19:01.683 --> 19:04.102
It doesn't? But the sign--

19:04.311 --> 19:09.525
ls of a fable of an ancient herd
called the Majestique.

19:09.733 --> 19:12.945
They were said to roam wild somewhere
in these mountains.

19:13.862 --> 19:16.865
The story is that they are descended
from a breed...

19:17.074 --> 19:20.160
...created over a thousand years ago...

19:20.327 --> 19:24.289
...especia||y for the princesses
of the Kieburg royalty...

19:24.498 --> 19:27.000
<i>...and fiercely loyal to them.</i>

19:27.209 --> 19:29.461
<i>They protected them from harm...</i>

19:29.670 --> 19:34.424
<i>...and the princesses were just
as devoted and protective of them.</i>

19:34.591 --> 19:37.886
<i>A strong fearless breed.</i>

19:38.095 --> 19:42.349
<i>They were said
to have such superb jumping skill...</i>

19:42.558 --> 19:47.062
<i>...that they almost seemed to fly.</i>

19:51.108 --> 19:55.153
<i>They are known by the strange pink streak
in their manes.</i>

19:55.362 --> 19:59.825
<i>The smartest, the fastest,
the bravest horses ever known to man.</i>

19:59.992 --> 20:01.702
[NEIGHS]

20:03.453 --> 20:05.956
Many doubt that they were ever real...

20:06.164 --> 20:10.586
...since none has ever been caught
or even photographed.

20:10.794 --> 20:14.423
-But what about the painting?
-Heh. What of it?

20:14.631 --> 20:18.635
There are also paintings
of fairies and mermaids, no?

20:18.844 --> 20:22.556
So you don't think the Majestique horses
are real?

20:22.723 --> 20:29.438
Mm. Once, when I was a child, I thought I saw--

20:29.646 --> 20:32.399
-Nonsense. Foolish twaddle.
BARBIE: Huh?

20:32.608 --> 20:35.402
You have always believed in fairy tales, Etienne.

20:35.611 --> 20:39.323
Philippe. Hmph.
How dare you defile my stable...

20:39.531 --> 20:42.576
...you festering boil on a baboon's backside?

20:42.784 --> 20:47.414
-And you are the hair of a pig's nostril.
-I spit on the toe of your uncle.

20:47.623 --> 20:50.584
I stuff your nose with cabbages.

20:50.792 --> 20:55.797
Hi, my name's Barbie.
I gather you two know each other.

20:57.507 --> 20:59.509
<i>Excuse-moi, mademoiselle.</i>

20:59.718 --> 21:05.057
I am Monsieur Philippe, riding master
extraordinaire of L'Ecole Montagne.

21:05.223 --> 21:06.892
[WHINNIES]

21:07.100 --> 21:09.978
I speak up only because this pig
of a dog of a mule...

21:10.187 --> 21:13.315
...fills your head with phooey-hooey.

21:14.316 --> 21:19.446
There is no such breed as the Majestique
and there never was.

21:19.780 --> 21:21.281
No horse is that remarkable.

21:21.490 --> 21:24.409
They are merely dumb beasts meant
to serve their masters...

21:24.618 --> 21:27.037
...and fear the riding crop.

21:27.245 --> 21:28.664
[NEIGHING]

21:30.290 --> 21:36.630
But why do you ask about Majestiques?
Have you seen something?

21:36.838 --> 21:39.466
Me? Um, uh.... Ha-ha.

21:39.633 --> 21:43.095
How could I see something that doesn't exist?

21:45.305 --> 21:49.434
Yes, of course, utter foolishness.

21:49.643 --> 21:52.312
Etienne, it is chilly.

21:52.521 --> 21:56.650
- Maman says to wear your sweater.
-Tell her the soup was yummy.

21:56.858 --> 22:00.195
PHILIPPE: And how was the baguette?
ETIENNE: I did not receive a baguette.

22:00.404 --> 22:02.155
PHILIPPE:
Exactly.

22:24.761 --> 22:27.055
[CHUCKLES]

22:35.522 --> 22:40.110
Hmm. Come on, Finian, let's go home.

22:46.450 --> 22:48.660
[ANIMALS RUNNING
AND LEAVES RUSTLING]

22:50.495 --> 22:51.830
What is it?

22:52.956 --> 22:53.999
[HORSE GROWLS]

22:54.166 --> 22:56.084
[FINIAN NEIGHING]

22:56.251 --> 22:57.961
[GASPS]

22:59.921 --> 23:02.466
Finian, come back!

23:03.967 --> 23:05.802
[GROWLING]

23:06.011 --> 23:08.263
Oh, boy.

23:08.764 --> 23:10.766
[WOLVES GROWLING]

23:26.406 --> 23:28.325
[GRUNTING]

23:34.706 --> 23:35.832
[HORSE APPROACHING]

23:35.999 --> 23:37.626
[HORSE NEIGHING]

23:44.091 --> 23:45.550
[SNORTS]

23:47.844 --> 23:48.887
[GROWLS]

23:49.054 --> 23:50.430
[NEIGHS]

23:54.601 --> 23:57.771
[NEIGHS]

24:08.031 --> 24:12.410
So you are real. I knew it.

24:13.787 --> 24:15.455
Thank you.

24:15.664 --> 24:17.374
[NEIGHS]

24:20.794 --> 24:22.337
[CLICKS TONGUE THEN WHISTLES]

24:22.504 --> 24:24.881
[SNORTING]

24:27.008 --> 24:30.387
Heh. My hero.

24:33.306 --> 24:34.349
[ETIENNE SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

24:34.516 --> 24:36.226
Straighten up, <i>Mam'seI/e</i> Stacie.

24:38.270 --> 24:42.023
Legs pressed together, weight forward.

24:43.275 --> 24:44.526
[ETIENNE SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

24:44.734 --> 24:48.280
Now pull your horse back to a walk, then stop.

24:48.697 --> 24:50.323
Whoa.

24:51.283 --> 24:54.077
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

24:54.244 --> 24:55.620
Don't you know how to whoa?

24:55.829 --> 24:58.874
No, no, no, mam'selle, we do not yank the reins.

24:59.082 --> 25:00.417
You will only make her--

25:00.584 --> 25:03.545
Hey, hey, he)â

25:04.880 --> 25:06.715
[STUDENTS LAUGHING]

25:07.174 --> 25:08.717
[PEPPER NEIGHING]

25:11.553 --> 25:13.722
[SIGHS THEN SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

25:14.347 --> 25:17.225
Aunt Marlene, I need a new horse.

25:17.434 --> 25:19.186
Mine is busted.

25:19.394 --> 25:24.024
No, Stacie, Pepper is your horse
and she chose you for a reason.

25:24.232 --> 25:26.985
Yeah, because she craves
my public humiliation.

25:27.194 --> 25:29.196
She won't do anything I tell her to.

25:29.404 --> 25:34.034
Of course she will. When she wants to.

25:35.493 --> 25:36.953
[NEIGHING]

25:46.630 --> 25:47.797
Tsk, tsk, hyah!

26:12.739 --> 26:13.949
HVah!

26:19.162 --> 26:20.622
[FINIAN SNORTS]

26:30.423 --> 26:33.093
BARBIE:
I know you're here somewhere.

26:37.138 --> 26:39.099
[HORSE NEIGHING]

26:47.565 --> 26:49.109
[GASPS]

26:49.276 --> 26:51.027
[NEIGHING]

26:54.239 --> 26:56.616
[PANTING THEN NEIGHING]

27:02.956 --> 27:05.125
It's all right.

27:05.333 --> 27:08.336
Everything's going to be just fine.

27:08.503 --> 27:12.048
Let me help you, okay?

27:12.257 --> 27:15.343
Wow. You really did get stuck, didn't you?

27:16.219 --> 27:17.345
That must hurt.

27:17.554 --> 27:18.555
[NEIGHING]

27:18.763 --> 27:21.349
Easy girl, easy.

27:22.017 --> 27:23.893
That's it.

27:25.312 --> 27:27.314
[HUMMING]

27:31.401 --> 27:36.364
[SINGING]
<i>Fais</i> dodo, t'auras <i>du</i> lolo

27:36.573 --> 27:42.829
<i>Fais dodo, ma petite soeur</i>

27:43.038 --> 27:49.377
<i>Fais dodo, t'auras du Iolo</i>

27:58.887 --> 28:00.305
[GRUNTING]

28:00.513 --> 28:02.265
[NEIGHING]

28:02.557 --> 28:03.683
[HORSE GRUNTING]

28:07.354 --> 28:10.106
Oh, you're bleeding.

28:12.859 --> 28:16.988
I just want to help you. It's okay.

28:21.868 --> 28:23.870
[HUMMING]

28:28.666 --> 28:32.879
I owe you this for the wolves.

28:33.129 --> 28:35.131
[SNORTING]

28:37.175 --> 28:39.677
You're so majestic.

28:39.886 --> 28:44.724
I think I'll call you Majesty.

28:48.853 --> 28:50.647
Okay, one more, Barnaby.

28:50.855 --> 28:54.025
And this time a little more presidential.

28:54.234 --> 28:55.902
[HORSE APPROACHING]

28:56.986 --> 29:00.073
Hey, Tech Girl. Ever put that thing down?

29:00.281 --> 29:03.368
Oh, look, Barnaby, you have a visitor.

29:03.576 --> 29:04.619
[BLEATS]

29:04.786 --> 29:07.622
Did you come to have your official portrait taken,
monkey boy?

29:09.332 --> 29:13.044
Ooh. That one will look good on a baboon,
don't you think?

29:13.962 --> 29:15.171
[BLEATS]

29:15.338 --> 29:19.843
Heh. You may be good with a tablet,
but I'll bet I can outride you any day.

29:20.051 --> 29:22.387
You're on. I'll bring the bananas.

29:22.595 --> 29:25.932
Right now, I have some work to do
on your portrait.

29:26.599 --> 29:28.268
See you.

29:29.811 --> 29:33.565
ls he looking? Don't look.

29:33.898 --> 29:36.067
[SWEEPING]

29:37.902 --> 29:39.946
[NEIGHING]

29:40.113 --> 29:43.032
Dinner in a second.

29:44.200 --> 29:45.243
[GRUNTS]

29:45.410 --> 29:48.121
Oh. Chelsea?

29:48.329 --> 29:51.916
-Shh. I'm hiding from Dash.
-Oh.

29:54.419 --> 29:56.254
Why are we hiding from Dash?

29:56.463 --> 29:59.090
Because she keeps eating my hair.

29:59.299 --> 30:00.884
It looks fine to me.

30:01.092 --> 30:04.179
Yeah, but she follows me around everywhere...

30:04.387 --> 30:06.097
...and nibbles on my pigtails...

30:06.306 --> 30:11.269
...and gets horse slobber all over my head.

30:11.644 --> 30:13.229
I see.

30:13.771 --> 30:14.981
[SNIFFS THEN GASPS]

30:15.148 --> 30:21.279
-Does your hair smell like candy?
-Marshmallow Tresses Shampoo.

30:21.488 --> 30:22.989
My favourite.

30:23.198 --> 30:26.868
It's made with real live marshmallows.

30:27.035 --> 30:28.953
Ah. Well, that explains it.

30:29.162 --> 30:32.290
-Dash loves marshmallows too.
-She does?

30:32.499 --> 30:34.542
Oh, my, yes.

30:34.751 --> 30:38.796
In fact, you two have lots of things in common.

30:39.005 --> 30:43.301
She loves pretty ribbons,
and things that glitter and anything pink.

30:43.510 --> 30:45.762
Perhaps you should give her another chance.

30:45.970 --> 30:47.931
I don't know.

30:48.139 --> 30:51.184
She really, really likes you, Chelsea.

30:51.392 --> 30:57.732
And, you know, I bet she'd look wonderful
in sparkly bows.

30:57.941 --> 31:00.026
You think?

31:00.235 --> 31:03.530
Hmm. Maybe I could pretty her up.

31:03.738 --> 31:07.992
We could start with a manicure
and then braid her hair.

31:08.159 --> 31:12.497
Oh. And then I could use the sparkles,
and then maybe I could give her....

31:14.123 --> 31:15.750
[NEIGHING]

31:28.805 --> 31:30.348
Hmm?

31:32.308 --> 31:33.685
<i>Hmm.</i>

31:33.977 --> 31:35.395
[GASPS]

31:50.702 --> 31:52.704
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

32:00.545 --> 32:03.006
Yeah, way to go!

32:04.591 --> 32:06.593
I got this.

32:11.264 --> 32:13.850
Excellent form, Marie, as always.

32:14.058 --> 32:16.769
Pity you are too young to compete. Hmm?

32:16.978 --> 32:18.730
<i>Mam'seI/e</i> Stacie, you are next.

32:18.938 --> 32:22.233
Remember, you and your mount are as one.

32:22.442 --> 32:24.360
You must be the horse.

32:24.527 --> 32:25.737
[SQUEALS]

32:25.903 --> 32:27.655
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

32:29.198 --> 32:30.533
<i>Now, allez vous.</i>

32:35.955 --> 32:37.373
[APPLAUDING]

32:38.249 --> 32:40.460
All right. Now we're talking.

32:45.548 --> 32:48.801
Oh, man, I am so good at this.

32:55.642 --> 32:56.684
Whoa!

32:56.851 --> 32:58.686
[WATER SPLASHING]

32:58.895 --> 32:59.937
[PEPPER SNORTING]

33:00.104 --> 33:01.189
Ugh. Yuck.

33:01.356 --> 33:02.607
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

33:02.774 --> 33:04.567
<i>Mam'seI/e Stacie.</i>

33:07.695 --> 33:09.364
Perhaps I did not explain.

33:09.572 --> 33:14.911
You are supposed to jump
through the hedge with the horse.

33:15.119 --> 33:16.371
[NEIGHING]

33:19.832 --> 33:22.919
SKIPPER: Ha-ha.
And that's for this year's holiday card.

33:23.086 --> 33:24.420
[BOTH LAUGH]

33:25.254 --> 33:27.090
[HORSE NEIGHING]

33:35.473 --> 33:36.724
HVah!

33:39.227 --> 33:41.145
[PHILIPPE CHUCKLES]

33:41.312 --> 33:42.563
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

33:42.730 --> 33:46.401
Now, show me what you've found.

33:46.693 --> 33:47.819
[WHISTLES]

33:54.701 --> 33:56.160
MAX: It's classical.
MARIE: So boring.

33:56.327 --> 33:58.955
MAX: It's what you see in races.
They put roses on the horses.

33:59.163 --> 34:01.708
I don't care what they're for.

34:01.874 --> 34:04.752
MAX:
Since mother left it to us to decide...

34:04.919 --> 34:06.713
...I think the theme for the dance...

34:06.879 --> 34:10.925
...sh0u|d be "Alpine Primroses in Summertime."

34:11.134 --> 34:13.177
I was thinking "Robot Samurai."

34:13.344 --> 34:15.179
[DOGS BARKING]

34:15.888 --> 34:18.433
What does that have to do with a horse show?

34:18.641 --> 34:23.228
What do you think robot samurai ride around on,
skateboards?

34:23.438 --> 34:25.440
Really? You can't put a robot on a horse.

34:25.606 --> 34:27.984
- It would fall off.
MARIE: Why not?

34:28.693 --> 34:30.319
[GRUNTS]

34:31.237 --> 34:33.531
[WHISTLES THEN COUGHS]

34:33.697 --> 34:34.991
Ahem. Horse.

34:36.909 --> 34:38.411
[SCREAMS]

34:41.038 --> 34:43.458
[NEIGHING]

34:46.668 --> 34:49.672
[HEAVYNN GATES' "YOU'RE THE ONE"
PLAYING]

34:54.927 --> 34:58.556
<i>Some people say you can't be found</i>

34:58.723 --> 35:01.267
<i>You're not around</i>

35:02.268 --> 35:07.857
<i>Some people say that you're not real
A fairy tale</i>

35:09.525 --> 35:12.945
<i>They say that dreams are for sleeping</i>

35:13.154 --> 35:16.657
<i>I'm wide awake and believing</i>

35:16.866 --> 35:22.622
<i>Open my eyes and see
You're right in front of me</i>

35:22.830 --> 35:23.873
<i>You're the one</i>

35:26.709 --> 35:30.421
<i>You're the one, I've known all along</i>

35:30.630 --> 35:32.048
<i>You're the one</i>

35:32.256 --> 35:34.050
[LAUGHING]

35:34.258 --> 35:37.094
<i>You're the one, you're all that I want</i>

35:38.179 --> 35:41.516
<i>You're wild and free,
Strong enough for</i> me

35:41.682 --> 35:47.980
<i>And what we have will never be undone</i>

35:48.981 --> 35:50.566
<i>You're the one</i>

35:52.693 --> 35:56.197
<i>Like the morning needs the dawn,
You keep me holding on</i>

35:56.364 --> 35:58.616
<i>Run away with me</i>

36:00.409 --> 36:05.498
<i>Oh, what you are to me,
You show me how to see tomorrow</i>

36:05.706 --> 36:08.334
<i>Tomorrow, tomorrow</i>

36:08.501 --> 36:09.710
[WHOOPING]

36:11.045 --> 36:13.798
<i>You're the one</i>

36:14.632 --> 36:18.427
<i>You're the one, I've known all along</i>

36:18.594 --> 36:21.931
<i>You're the one</i>

36:22.098 --> 36:25.560
<i>You're the one</i>

36:25.726 --> 36:29.063
<i>You're the one</i>

36:29.272 --> 36:35.319
<i>You're the one</i>

36:43.494 --> 36:45.288
<i>Oh, you're the one</i>

36:51.210 --> 36:53.421
[NEIGHING]

37:01.012 --> 37:03.097
Where are you taking me?

37:08.936 --> 37:10.980
[HORSE NEIGHING IN DISTANCE]

37:17.570 --> 37:18.613
[GASPS]

37:18.779 --> 37:20.239
Oh....

37:23.659 --> 37:27.413
Majestiques, a whole herd of them.

37:27.747 --> 37:29.999
[NEIGHING]

37:30.207 --> 37:32.209
[ALL NEIGHING]

37:54.732 --> 37:56.734
[TAPPING ON KEYPAD]

38:07.828 --> 38:09.246
[SIGHS]

38:09.413 --> 38:13.751
- Something wrong, Aunt Marlene?
-it's nothing, dear.

38:14.293 --> 38:18.464
-Have you had your lunch yet?
-Something is wrong.

38:18.673 --> 38:22.677
Please tell me.
I'm a teenager so I'll never let this drop.

38:24.220 --> 38:25.262
[SIGHS]

38:25.429 --> 38:27.974
I'm afraid it's nothing you can help with.

38:28.182 --> 38:31.352
The fact is, I may have to sell the academy.

38:31.560 --> 38:34.230
Sell it? But why?

38:34.438 --> 38:36.899
Too many bills, too few students.

38:37.108 --> 38:41.779
I have tried to hold on, but two weeks ago,
I got an offer for the place...

38:41.988 --> 38:44.615
...from Madame Cheynet of Ecole Montagne.

38:44.824 --> 38:47.326
No doubt Philippe's idea.

38:47.535 --> 38:50.705
He has never forgiven Etienne
for coming here...

38:50.913 --> 38:55.459
...and if we don't win the tournament prize money,
I'll have to accept.

38:57.253 --> 39:00.715
You're not gonna do it, are you?

39:01.382 --> 39:03.592
Alpine has been in our family for generations.

39:03.801 --> 39:06.053
I was born here.

39:06.220 --> 39:08.764
I'd be crushed to lose it...

39:10.016 --> 39:12.268
...but I may have no choice.

39:12.476 --> 39:15.396
They're giving me until Tuesday
to accept their offer.

39:15.604 --> 39:17.857
Won't winning the race bring in new students?

39:18.065 --> 39:20.693
Of course, that would be wonderful.

39:20.860 --> 39:24.780
But truthfully, we haven't won a tournament
in 11 years.

39:24.989 --> 39:29.035
This year, you've got a secret weapon,
the Roberts sisters.

39:29.243 --> 39:32.288
Can you hold off the sale
just until after the tournament?

39:32.496 --> 39:33.622
I can try.

39:33.831 --> 39:36.417
-But, Skipper, really.
-No time to talk.

39:36.625 --> 39:39.336
I've got to see a girl about a race.

39:53.726 --> 39:55.895
[MAJESTIC NEIGHING]

39:58.522 --> 39:59.565
[SIGHS]

39:59.732 --> 40:01.108
[SKIPPER WHISTLING]

40:01.275 --> 40:03.986
-Way to go, Barbie.
-Skipper.

40:04.195 --> 40:06.489
That is one awesome horse.

40:06.697 --> 40:11.410
Oh, Skipper, it was amazing.
We were flying, soaring.

40:11.619 --> 40:15.372
This is the horse I've been looking for all my life.

40:15.581 --> 40:19.251
But you can't say a word about her.
Not until I say so.

40:19.460 --> 40:22.630
-Barbie, something's happened--
-Promise you won't.

40:24.173 --> 40:26.425
Pinky pledge-

40:27.676 --> 40:31.889
-When exactly are we too old for that?
-Heh. Never.

40:32.098 --> 40:35.434
Okay, my beautiful Majesty, see you tomorrow.

40:35.643 --> 40:38.104
Go on now.

40:39.980 --> 40:43.150
Majesty, I like that.

40:43.692 --> 40:47.238
But look, there's something
I really need to tell you.

40:47.863 --> 40:51.826
BARBIE:
Lose the academy? That's terrible.

40:52.034 --> 40:54.578
-Poor Aunt Marlene.
-Exactly.

40:54.787 --> 40:57.164
Which is why Alpine has to win this tournament.

40:57.373 --> 41:01.418
I'm even violating my strict anti-involvement policy
by entering dressage.

41:01.585 --> 41:04.088
That's perfect. You're fantastic at dressage.

41:04.296 --> 41:06.632
And that's why you have to run
in the steeplechase.

41:06.841 --> 41:10.052
You riding Majesty
would totally demolish the competition.

41:10.261 --> 41:13.806
Skipper, I can't. Etienne is riding for Alpine.

41:14.014 --> 41:15.391
It's tradition.

41:15.558 --> 41:18.727
And besides, Majesty needs to stay a secret...

41:18.936 --> 41:20.896
...at least till I get her back to Malibu.

41:21.105 --> 41:22.773
A secret? Why?

41:22.982 --> 41:27.528
Because Philippe will recognise what she is
and know there must be more like her.

41:27.736 --> 41:31.740
After we leave, I don't want her herd
hunted down and broken.

41:31.949 --> 41:35.327
So Majestiques need to stay a fairy tale.

41:35.536 --> 41:37.329
But what about the steeplechase?

41:37.538 --> 41:40.124
What about us winning the tournament
for Aunt Marlene?

41:40.332 --> 41:42.084
Look, Etienne is a champion rider...

41:42.293 --> 41:44.378
...and remember, there's more than one event.

41:44.587 --> 41:45.796
With you doing dressage...

41:46.005 --> 41:49.175
...I'm sure Alpine's got everything they need.

41:53.387 --> 41:56.557
[SEBASTIAN GRUNTING]

41:57.808 --> 41:58.893
[BOTH BARKING]

42:03.063 --> 42:05.441
[WHEELS ROLLING]

42:15.367 --> 42:18.579
Stacie? You're not practising for Saturday?

42:18.787 --> 42:22.458
Yeah, I don't know.
I'm kind off horseback riding for now.

42:22.666 --> 42:27.463
Really? But aren't you signed up
for the cross-country trial?

42:27.671 --> 42:31.926
Actually, I was thinking
about dropping out of that.

42:32.134 --> 42:33.552
It's not really my thing.

42:34.678 --> 42:36.555
Okay, Stacie, what's wrong?

42:36.722 --> 42:39.433
Since when don't you like to compete?

42:39.642 --> 42:43.354
